The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 30: O.P. Bhatt, managing director of State Bank of India, was today appointed chairman of the bank. Bhatt replaces A.K. Purwar, who retired as the chairman of the country?s largest commercial bank on May 31 this year. T.S. Bhatacharya, another managing director of the bank, had been working as the acting chairman after Purwar?s retirement.

 Mumbai, June 30: To curb mutual funds from launching similar funds under new names, Sebi has asked the trustees of the asset management companies to certify the scheme/fund approved by them.

 Mumbai, June 30: India?s forex reserves decreased by $1.073 billion to $161.960 billion during the week ended June 23 against $163.033 billion during the week ended June 16.

 New Delhi, June 30: The country?s fiscal deficit stood at Rs 72,088 crore for the first two months of the current financial year, which was 48 per cent of the budget estimate of Rs 1,48,686 crore for the whole of 2006-07. 

 Geneva, June 30: India has threatened to walk out of the WTO meeting, convened to discuss farm and industrial tariff issues, with the US refusing to agree to wider cuts in farm subsidies. ?I?ll ring up my travel agent and get a flight home,? said commerce minister Kamal Nath.




